New Records: De'Aaron Fox's 109 points are the most over a two-game span in Sacramento Kings franchise history, passing DeMarcus Cousins.
Key Match Events: De'Aaron Fox scored 49 points, leading the Sacramento Kings to a 121-117 win over the Utah Jazz.
The Kings trailed 89-78 in the third quarter but came back in the fourth to take a 118-116 lead on a Jordan McLaughlin 3-pointer with a minute left to play.
De'Aaron Fox made his first seven shots from the floor, including three 3-pointers in the first quarter, and had 26 points by halftime.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Kings made 19 of 41 shots (46.3%) from 3-point range.
DeMar DeRozan, Malik Monk, and Domantas Sabonis were sidelined for Sacramento, and Taylor Hendricks and Walker Kessler did not play for the Jazz.
